# Cursor AI Rules for Ergo Blockchain website

## STRICT RULE: NO FILE STRUCTURE CHANGES

**NEVER DO:**
- Move files between directories
- Rename files or folders
- Create new directories
- Delete existing files
- Change import paths between files
- Restructure the project layout
- Modify file extensions
- Change directory hierarchy
- Create new files
- Add new components to different directories
- Move components between folders
- Change file locations
- Reorganize any part of the file structure
- Create new folders or subdirectories

**ONLY ALLOWED:**
- Edit content inside existing files (text, code, comments)
- Modify existing code within files
- Fix bugs by changing code content
- Update configuration values within existing config files
- Add comments or documentation within existing files
- Refactor code within the same file
- Update dependencies in package.json (content only)
- Modify existing CSS/styling within files
- Change text content in existing files

**EXCEPTIONS:**
- Only if user **explicitly requests** structure changes
- Only after **explicit confirmation** from user
- Only for critical security fixes that require file moves

## Project Structure Rules

- Keep all files in their current locations
- Maintain existing import/export patterns
- Preserve directory naming conventions
- Don't reorganize components or pages
- Keep configuration files in root directory

## Development Guidelines

- Focus on content improvements, not structural changes
- Ask permission before any file operations
- Explain why changes are needed before applying
- Respect existing code organization
- Maintain backward compatibility

## Violation Consequences

If you violate this rule:
1. Stop immediately
2. Revert any changes made
3. Apologize to the user
4. Ask for explicit permission before proceeding

**Remember: This project structure is intentional and should not be modified without explicit user consent.**